 "awd_abstract_narration": "The proposed research will develop tools and methodologies that can be broadly applied for conducting integrated assessments of complex environmental issues in the United States and in other countries around the world, with specific application to Mexico City. The proposal focuses on four critical issues: (i) development of  integrated assessment methodologies and tools aimed at using the best available data and existing common and accepted models in order to produce policy-relevant results; (ii) development of  methods to couple urban, regional, and global air pollution models, particularly for aerosols; (iii) development of  methodologies to link emissions estimates and policy impacts in urban, regional and global contexts for energy, transportation, and industrial sectors; and (iv) development of  impact analysis methodologies for tailoring health effects damage functions based on composite US data to local conditions and demographics for use in policy analysis.\r\n\r\n",
